WEBVTT

00:01.525 --> 00:03.418
<i>Previously on Kyle XY...</i>

00:03.529 --> 00:04.792
So let me understand.

00:04.872 --> 00:06.853
The boy has no family that you know of.

00:06.933 --> 00:09.668
He doesn't communicate, and he was
found wandering alone in the city.

00:09.748 --> 00:11.904
But there is one more thing
we should see.

00:11.990 --> 00:14.156
- No belly button.
- I have a new patient,

00:14.236 --> 00:16.271
and I'm bringing him here
for a little while.

00:16.352 --> 00:18.639
- You don't know him.
- Don't want he touches my things.

00:18.719 --> 00:20.987
He's a very sweet, very special boy.

00:21.067 --> 00:23.447
He's this super brain... with amnesia.

00:23.527 --> 00:25.617
He can't understand the simplest things,

00:25.697 --> 00:27.928
but does calculus like it's 2 plus 2.

00:28.008 --> 00:29.810
He barely knows what
you're saying sometimes,

00:29.890 --> 00:31.973
but somehow speaks Chinese?

00:32.052 --> 00:35.139
Mom, I'm telling you, Kyle is not human.

00:35.250 --> 00:37.143
781227.

00:37.229 --> 00:39.491
Spelling out your alien birthday?

00:39.578 --> 00:40.782
It's you!

00:41.065 --> 00:43.696
1985?

00:43.893 --> 00:45.027
The guy in the photo.

00:45.107 --> 00:46.109
It's Adam Baylin.

00:46.189 --> 00:48.753
Adam Baylin has been
missing for 20 years.

00:49.035 --> 00:50.634
You gotta stop asking questions!

00:50.745 --> 00:52.923
If you don't, you're gonna put
your family in danger.

00:53.003 --> 00:54.853
- Who are you?
- It's Mom.

00:54.933 --> 00:56.759
The Peterson's live in Connecticut.

00:56.839 --> 00:58.136
I'll be ready to go by tomorrow.

00:58.216 --> 00:59.679
Now that I know, I'm ready.

00:59.759 --> 01:01.222
You're not telling me something.

01:01.302 --> 01:03.616
You've proven you can keep my secrets.

01:03.696 --> 01:06.503
If there was anything to tell,
don't you think I'd bring you in on it?

01:06.583 --> 01:08.283
- Thanks for everything.
- Take care, kid.

01:11.431 --> 01:14.576
I'll take care of 781227
and Adam Baylin.

01:14.656 --> 01:17.245
In the meantime, 781228

01:17.325 --> 01:19.261
is in excellent condition.

01:19.629 --> 01:20.710
What did you tell him?

01:20.790 --> 01:23.815
To go with the Petersons, it was the
only way to keep Tragers out of danger.

01:23.926 --> 01:25.234
You two are very good liars.

01:25.735 --> 01:27.115
It's our job.

01:30.249 --> 01:31.663
I'm Adam Baylin.

01:31.774 --> 01:34.167
- What do you want from me?
- What would you like to know?

01:34.247 --> 01:35.547
Everything.

